                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-126-victim696 t18260112-126-viclabel718"></join>. On the 7th of January, between ten and eleven o'clock, I went out with some bread - I returned between eleven and twelve, and as I was going up the steps I met the prisoner coming out, with my till in his hand, and 12s. 9d. in copper in it.(Till produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went in for a penny loaf, and a boy in the shop asked if I would have the till - I said I would.</p>
